-- Slovak Poll Shows Smer Party Would Win Majority, TA3 Reports
-- B y   R a d o s l a v   T o m e k
-- 2012-02-15T07:49:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/slovak-poll-shows-smer-party-would-win-majority-ta3-reports.html
Slovakia’s largest opposition party
Smer would win a majority in parliament ,  TA3  reported, citing
results of a poll it commissioned with Polis agency one month
before the elections.  Smer, led by former premier  Robert Fico , would muster 40.8
percent, representing 81 deputies in a 150-seat parliament, the
TV channel reported. Support for current Prime Minister  Iveta
Radicova ’s SDKU party fell to 5.1 percent, or 0.1 percentage
point above the threshold to be represented in parliament, TA3
said.  TA3 didn’t specify the details of the poll, nor its margin
of error. Slovakia holds elections on March 10.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
